
# Probability Distribution 
    # Probability distribution describes the probability of each possible outcomes in a scenario. 
    # Expected value = mean of a distribution = sum(each outcome * their probability) 
    # Probability = Selected area of probability distribution.
    # Discrete uniform distribution = Each outcome has same probability (?) 

# Law of large number: 
    # As the sample size increases, the sample mean will approach the expected mean, i.e theoretical mean. 
    

